The Inspector-General of Police, IGP, Mohammed Adamu, has ordered the Federal Capital Territory, FCT, Abuja, Command of the Nigeria Police Force to seal off the National Secretariat of the ruling All Progressives Congress, APC. Vanguard learned that the order was necessitated by the need to ensure public order and safety in and around the secretariat. At press time, some of the staff told Vanguard that they were preparing to leave the premises. The order might not be unconnected with the party’s leadership confusion since no fewer than three persons have been named in connection with the chairmanship position. While the Court of Appeal upheld a lower court’s ruling suspending Comrade Adams Oshiomhole as APC National Chairman, Giadom is laying a claim to the position, while the National Working Committee picked Ajimobi as the Chairman in an acting capacity. Vanguard OLEH—CHAIRMAN of All Progressives Congress, APC, in Delta State, Prophet Jones Ode Erue, has lambasted the state police command for denying him access to the party’s secretariat in Asaba to inaugurate the party’s local government executives. July 25, 2018 In "News" Armed policemen yesterday, cordoned off the secretariat of the All Progressives Congress, APC in Ondo state as the crisis over the sack of the State Chairman, Mr Isaac Kekemeke deepened. August 18, 2016 In "News" ABUJA— FOLLOWING allegations against him on corruption, nepotism, misuse of office, misappropriation of funds, illegal promotion, posting of senior officers by the Chairman, Senate Committee on Navy, Senator Isah Hamman Misau (APC, Bauchi Central), the Inspector- General of Police, IGP, Ibrahim Idris will today appear before the Senate Ad-hoc Committee… October 25, 2017 In "News"